00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:18.500
&gt;&gt; Candice Millard: Yeah.

00:18:18.500 --> 00:18:19.800
Exactly, yeah.

00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:21.100
To look-- and look like--

00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:23.010
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Yardley: And he
went to South Africa with what?

00:18:23.010 --> 00:18:24.990 position:56%
Cases of champagne and whiskey and--

00:18:24.990 --> 00:18:26.460
&gt;&gt; Candice Millard:
Yeah, and his valet and,

00:18:26.460 --> 00:18:28.580
you know, 10-year-old whiskey.

00:18:28.580 --> 00:18:31.380
Right. So, he-- You know,
he's willing to risk his life

00:18:31.380 --> 00:18:36.390
but he doesn't-- he doesn't want
to be uncivilized while he's at it.

00:18:36.390 --> 00:18:40.620
But what was interesting about him
to me at this point in his life is

00:18:40.620 --> 00:18:44.090 position:56%
that if you look at pictures of
him, you almost don't recognize him.

00:18:44.090 --> 00:18:46.360
So obviously when we think
of Winston Churchill,

00:18:46.360 --> 00:18:48.390
we think of the older ones
and Churchill during war

00:18:48.390 --> 00:18:50.770 position:56%
and he is overweight and he is older

00:18:50.770 --> 00:18:53.830
and he's got his cigar
and his whiskey.

00:18:53.830 --> 00:18:56.690
And this one, he is
young and he has red hair

00:18:56.690 --> 00:18:58.360
and he is sort of energetic.

00:18:58.360 --> 00:19:01.910
And he is the one throwing
himself into war.

00:19:01.910 --> 00:19:07.780
But inside, inside he was already
the Winston Churchill we know

00:19:07.780 --> 00:19:13.100
and it's fascinating to read the
letters that he wrote at that time.

00:19:13.100 --> 00:19:16.380
And there was one in particular
that he wrote to Pamela Plowden.

00:19:16.380 --> 00:19:20.440
So he ran for parliament before
the Boer War and he lost.

00:19:20.440 --> 00:19:23.900
But during the election, and he
is loving it, he's loving all

00:19:23.900 --> 00:19:26.360
of these opportunities
to be on a stage.

00:19:26.360 --> 00:19:29.740
And he writes to her, he says, "You
know, I don't know what's going

00:19:29.740 --> 00:19:31.040
to happen with the election.

00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:33.250
I don't know what the
outcome will be.

00:19:33.250 --> 00:19:38.090
But with every speech I give,
I feel my growing powers."

00:19:38.090 --> 00:19:39.760
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Yardley: Something
